"content": "<p>A young, untrained horse or donkey, associated in Scripture with humility or peace.</p>\n<h2>A colt is a young donkey</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:12\">JOB 11:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:11\">GEN 49:11</a></p>\n<h2>The use of a colt by the coming king</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:2-Matt21:7\">MAT 21:2–21:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:2-Mark11:7\">MRK 11:2–11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:30-Luke19:35\">LUK 19:30–19:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:15\">JHN 12:15</a></p>",
